            <thetext>Currently, it is very inconvenient to add/remove tests or browsers to the matrix. It involves copying a lot of markup. Also, continuous numbers are included in the markup but get replaced by a script, which can be confusing.

I suggest to separate view and data by storing browsers and tests in an easily maintainable JSON structure. For generating the markup, qx.bom.Template can be used.

Moreover, style properties are scattered over inline style attributes and style element in the head of each test. This should be improved by referencing an external CSS file.</thetext>
